======================================================================
SUMMARY STATISTICS
======================================================================

  delta_vs_disjoint = 0 ALWAYS: True

  For disjoint-pair-preserving changes (delta_vs_disjoint=0):
  delta_i2 is a BILINEAR form in multiplicity changes
  = sum over disjoint VS pairs of (delta_m_i * m_j' + m_i * delta_m_j)

  Possible disjoint VS pair types at n=8:
    (c3, c3): need 6 vertices, possible
    (c3, c5): need 8 vertices = n, possible (tight!)
    Others: impossible (need > 8 vertices)

  Example 1 disjoint pair types:
    (c3, c3) pairs: 28
    (c3, c5) pairs: 10

